 New BNL estimates of the covariances in the resonances region    1325 1451
 were obtained using kernel approach up to 845 keV. Uncertainties 1325 1451
 of neutron resonance parameters as well as the scattering radius 1325 1451
 R' were taken from Atlas of Neutron Resonances.                  1325 1451
                                                                  1325 1451
 In the fast neutron region new covariances were prepared using   1325 1451
 experimental uncertainties below 8 MeV and EMPIRE/KALMAN         1325 1451
 approach above. There are many experimental data for total       1325 1451
 cross sections, far too many for the KALMAN filter to handle.    1325 1451
 However, the ENDF/B-VII.0 follows the fluctuating experimental   1325 1451
 data all the way up to ~8 MeV. The fluctuations are still easy   1325 1451
 to follow in this region, and several different experiments are  1325 1451
 in good agreement. It was decided to treat this region (for      1325 1451
 total and elastic) with one correlated block, with uncertainty   1325 1451
 of 3% (suggested systematic uncertainty of normalization for     1325 1451
 both Cierjacks and Schwartz experiments). Above 8 MeV,           1325 1451
 uncertainties come from EMPIRE/KALMAN.                           1325 1451
                                                                  1325 1451
 Other channels do not have very much experimental data. For      1325 1451
 inelastic scattering and capture the data are inconsistent or    1325 1451
 discrepant and it was decided to use purely model-based          1325 1451
 covariances for these channels (no including experimental        1325 1451
 data). Thus capture uncertainties are based on EMPIRE/KALMAN     1325 1451
 from 845 keV up.                                                 1325 1451
